<!--What is the return value from a call to node.removeChild()? What can you do with it? Show sample code to demonstrate how you might store the return value in a variable then use it. -->


node.removeChild() is a method for removing all of the child nodes of the removed node.

You must have a reference to a parent node with removeChild()

Ex.   function removeListFirstChild() {
    listNode.removeChild(listNode.firstChild);
}
  This first function, directly above, calls for removing only the first child from the listNode.

        function removalAllListChildren() {
            while (listNode.firstChild) {
                listNode.removeChild(listNode.firstChild);
            }
        }

This second function, directly above, calls for the removal of all children in the listNode.  -->